The paper proposes a deep learning model for product compatibility and function satisfiability analysis using a question and answering corpus. This involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the challenges of linguistic patterns and appropriate fusion of questions and answers, which are also relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
